articles.author: Tom Polansek
articles.description: The United States is importing record amounts of beef this year and exporting less after ranchers slashed the nation's cattle herd to its lowest level in decades, tightening margins for meat companies like Tyson Foods (TSN.N).
articles.title: US reduces beef exports as cattle herd shrinks, squeezing Tyson Foods

articles.author: Pete Schroeder
articles.description: A ransomware attack on Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) disrupted some trades in the U.S. Treasury market on Thursday, the Treasury Department said.
articles.title: Ransomware attack on China's ICBC disrupts Treasury market trades

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Workers belonging to the United Auto Workers (UAW) at General Motors' (GM.N) Flint assembly plant in Michigan have narrowly voted against a proposed contract with the automaker, the union's local chapter said.
articles.title: UAW workers at GM's Flint assembly narrowly vote against new labor deal

articles.author: Dan Burns
articles.description: U.S. consumer sentiment fell for a fourth straight month in November and households' expectations for inflation rose again, with their medium-term outlook for price pressures shooting to the highest level in more than a dozen years, a survey showed on Friday.
articles.title: US consumer sentiment drops again in November, inflation expectations rise

articles.author: Raphael Satter
articles.description: Private spy firm Black Cube was behind a hidden video campaign that used LinkedIn to target Hungarian activists and journalists leading to last year's election in the central European country, the professional networking site said on Thursday.
articles.title: LinkedIn says spy firm targeted Hungarian activists, journalists before 2022 election

articles.author: Stephen Nellis
articles.description: Humane, a Silicon Valley startup with a star-studded list of co-founders and executives, on Thursday released a $699 device that aims to bring cutting-edge artificial intelligence to a lapel near you.
articles.title: Wearable 'Ai Pin' launched by Humane, backed by ex-Apple execs and Microsoft

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The German parliament on Friday approved the implementation of a global minimum corporate tax, as part of an international deal to ensure large companies pay a minimum tax rate of 15%.
articles.title: Germany approves global minimum corporate tax

articles.author: Special Reports
articles.description: Reuters documented more than 600 workplace injuries at SpaceX. Employees say they’re paying the price for Elon Musk’s push to reach Mars at breakneck speed.
articles.title: At SpaceX, worker injuries soar in Elon Musk’s rush to Mars

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Steve Holland
articles.description: Gaza officials said Israel launched air strikes on or near at least three hospitals on Friday, further stressing the Palestinian enclave's precarious health system as it struggles to cope with thousands of people wounded or displaced in Israel's war against Hamas militants.
articles.title: Gaza officials say hospitals come under new Israeli attacks

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Nominations for the music industry's Grammy Awards were announced Friday. Here are a few selected categories.
articles.title: Leading nominations for 2024 Grammy Awards
